message: "If you use or cite this work, please use the following metadata."
title: "Comprehensive Statistics: A Complete Textbook"
authors:
  - family-names: "[LAST NAME]"
    given-names: "[FIRST NAME]"
version: "0.1.0"
date-released: "2026-07-02"
repository-code: "https://github.com/[USERNAME]/[REPO-NAME]"
abstract: >
  A graduate-to-practitioner-level statistics textbook covering 57 chapters
  across 17 parts — from probability foundations and descriptive statistics
  through Bayesian inference, causal methods, time series, machine learning,
  and epidemiology. Accompanied by a 65-section categorized reference of
  statistical tests and methods.
keywords:
  - statistics
  - textbook
  - Bayesian inference
  - causal inference
  - machine learning
  - epidemiology
  - time series
  - open textbook
